    "causal_summary": "The P0 MVP makes benchmarking config-driven and gates correctness, but its trust verdict uses a minimal single-sample heuristic, the dispatcher does not capture latency/tokens/cost (so \"token efficiency\" is approximated by word count), provider quirks (`--agent` omission, token-plan slugs) live in prose, and the fixture set is just a couple of T3 tasks. The research §5/§6/§4 roadmap calls these the P1 reliability tier.",
